              <title type="Incomplete" ref="LIT1688Job"/>
              <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
              <explicit>ዘኢዮብ። በዝየ፡ ተፈጸመ፡ ዘኢዮብ፡ መጽሐፍ። ወናሁ፡ ናስተበፅዖሙ፡ ለእለ፡ ተዐገሱ፡ 
              ትዕግስቶ፡ ለኢዮብ፡ ወርኢክሙ፡ መጠነ፡ ገብረ፡ ሎቱ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ወከመ፡ ብዙኅ፡ ምሕረቱ።
              ወስንኮርስ፡ አበዋየ፡ ባርኩኒ።</explicit>
              <rubric>From chapter 15, verse 1 on, the beginnings of the speeches are written in red</rubric>
              <note>The beginning until chapter 1, verse 6 is missing</note>
              <note>The text  has been translated from the <title ref="LIT2319Septua">Septuagint</title>  by a different translator than the historical books. </note>
                <note>Many passages have been corrected, such as:
              <p>In chap. 7, vers. 9; chap. 9, vers. 13 and chap. 17, vers. 13 and 16: ἅδης is translated by መቃብር፡ , everywhere else it has been corrected to ሲኦል</p>
                <p>In chap. 34, vers. 4 κρίσις is translated by ደይን፡ , in the corrected passages by ፍትሕ፡; see also <ref target="#a1.4"/> </p>
              <p>In chap. 9, vers. 2 and chap. 25, vers. 4, βροτός is translated by ንሡሕ፡ or ንጹሕ፡ , in the corrected passages by መዊት፡ </p></note>
              <note>There are also the following misunderstandments in the translation:
              <p>The name Βαλδὰδ ὁ Σαυχέων is always translated as በልዳዶስ፡ አውኬናዊ፡</p>
              <p>In chap. 28, vers. 16 the name Σωφίρ is translated as ኦፍር፡ </p>
                <p>In <locus target="40v."/> chap. 24, vers. 24 μολόχη has been transliterated, see also <ref target="#a1.2"/></p>
              <p>In chap. 40, vers. 12, κυπάρισσον has been transliterated</p>
                <p>In chap. 15, vers. 2 the translator read πρότερον (ቀዳሚሁ፡ ) instead of πότερον</p>
              <p>In chap. 18, vers. 15 the translator didn't understand κατασπαρήσονται τ(ወይዘርዎ፡ ምሥናዩ፡ ፈጣሪሁ፡), because he confused θεῖον with θεόν</p>
              <p>In chap. 38, vers. 31 he translated πλειάδος by ብዙኃን፡ ; and ὠρίωνος by ሙሐዘ፡ ማይ፡ </p>
              <p>In chap. 39, vers. 25, the translator read ἃρματι instead of ἃλματι </p>
              <p>Etc. </p>
              </note>
    <note>See also quotes from the text in <ref  target="#chapter6"/> and <ref target="#chapter30"/></note>
